        "timestamp": "2018-10-25 18:34:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> > Cloud owner can be specified directly by requestDetails.cloudConfiguration.cloudOwner\n > > if desired. I could not find much information about this issue at\n > > the original commit https://jira.onap.org/browse/SO-636 hash\n > > cd817ddd55b. Marcus can you send me an email to talk about what\n > > this was originally trying to solve?\n > \n > Hi Max,\n > \n > See this email chain https://lists.onap.org/g/onap-discuss/message/13243\n > \n > There was a proposal in Beijing to send vimId to SO during\n > instantiate requests, the change this if fixing was a bit early for\n > capabilities in VID.\n\nAdded cloudOwner as requestDetails.cloudConfiguration.cloudOwner \n\nThe original reason for accepting vimId was Bin Yang's proposal for components to use vimId in place of cloudRegion for \"Centralized Representation and Consistent Identification of Cloud Regions\" https://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Centralized+Representation+and+Consistent+Identification+of+Cloud+Regions+In+ONAP .",
        "patchset_number": 2
